Olive Oil
1 tin tinned cherry tomatoes
1 courgette
1 packet diced bacon
1 bunch thyme
1 packet garlic paste
½ bottle cream
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet spinach & ricotta tortellini
1 bunch basil

Drain and halve tomatoes. Chop courgette.
Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat.
Cook the diced bacon, tomatoes, courgette and thyme leaves, tossing, until tender, 4-5 mins.
Add garlic paste, cream (1/2 bottle for 2P / 1 bottle for 4P), chicken stock, spinach and Parmesan. Cook until slightly thickened, 1 min.

Meanwhile, boil a kettle of water.
Pour boiling water into a saucepan over high heat.
Bring to the boil, add tortellini and cook until al dente, 3 mins.

Add tortellini to the frying pan using a slotted spoon and toss to coat.
Divide pasta between bowls.
Top with chilli flakes (if using). Tear over basil.